    mindsetNote: 'Visible password fields are a shoulder-surfing risk. In open-plan offices, co-working spaces, or public areas, a plaintext password field is a direct exposure. Assessors reviewing custom applications should test authentication pages for basic security behaviors, not just server-side controls.',
