    explanation: 'MA.L2-3.7.2 requires providing controls on maintenance tools, techniques, mechanisms, and personnel. Unsupervised vendor access to a system containing CUI is a maintenance control gap — the contractor cannot verify what the vendor accessed, changed, or copied. PE.L2-3.10.3 applies to general visitor escorting; MA.L2-3.7.2 is the specific maintenance requirement. MA.L2-3.7.1 requires authorization (which the vendor presumably has), not supervision.',
