    explanation: 'CA.L2-3.12.1 requires periodically assessing security controls to determine if they are effective. This requires documented evidence that an assessment occurred, what was assessed, what was found, and what was done about it. Informal reviews without documentation cannot serve as evidence of compliance. There is no small-business exemption. CA.L2-3.12.1 does not require a C3PAO — that is the CMMC certification requirement; self-assessment against NIST SP 800-171 is the baseline.',
    mindsetNote: 'Periodic assessment is not the same as certification. CA.L2-3.12.1 requires that the contractor regularly asks: are our security controls actually working? The output should be documented findings and a POA&M. Think of it as an internal audit function. Size does not change the requirement — only the scope and rigor of the assessment.',
    sourceRef: 'NIST SP 800-171 Rev 2 §3.12.1',
