    mindsetNote: 'Encryption is not all equal. "We encrypt it" is not sufficient — the algorithm and implementation must be FIPS-validated. RC4 failing a FIPS requirement is not theoretical: real-world attacks can break RC4 traffic quickly. Know the approved algorithm families: AES for symmetric, RSA/ECC for asymmetric, SHA-2 or SHA-3 for hashing.',
