    explanation: 'SI.L2-3.14.1 requires identifying, reporting, and correcting information system flaws in a timely manner. A flat 90-day window for all vulnerabilities regardless of severity does not reflect a risk-based approach. A CVSS 9.1 critical vulnerability on a CUI-processing system is high risk and warrants prioritized, accelerated remediation. The policy itself is the finding — it fails to account for severity-based prioritization.',
    mindsetNote: 'One-size patch policies fail at the extremes. A critical RCE vulnerability should not wait 90 days. Most CMMC-aligned patch policies use a tiered approach: critical (7-30 days), high (30-60 days), medium/low (90+ days). Assessors should evaluate whether the patch policy reflects actual risk, not just whether a policy exists.',
