    mindsetNote: 'Perimeter monitoring catches attacks coming in; internal monitoring catches attacks already inside. The most dangerous phase of an attack — lateral movement and data staging — happens entirely on the internal network. East-west traffic monitoring (internal to internal) is required by SI.L2-3.14.6 and is the control that would have caught this attack.',
