    mindsetNote: 'This is one of the most commonly cited PS findings. Hiring timelines create pressure to grant access immediately. The correct approach is: (1) complete screening before access is granted, (2) use a provisional account with reduced permissions until screening clears, or (3) accept the risk in writing with compensating controls documented. As an assessor, compare three dates: hire date, access grant date, and screening completion date. If access preceded screening completion, the practice is not met — outcome is irrelevant.',
