    mindsetNote: 'Post-maintenance verification is an often-overlooked step. "Convenience for next time" is one of the most common rationalizations for security shortcuts. An assessor will ask: what is your process for verifying system state after a maintenance window closes? If the answer is "we trust the technician," that is a procedural gap in MA.L2-3.7.1.',
