    explanation: 'MA.L2-3.7.6 requires supervising the maintenance activities of personnel who do not have the required access authorization. Trust, tenure, and business relationship are not substitutes for the supervisory control required by this practice. HVAC technicians work in server rooms where CUI-processing systems are located — they have physical proximity to equipment and cabling even if they are not touching servers directly. The correct approach is escort and supervision throughout the visit, not granting unsupervised access. Option D (background check as prerequisite) is more restrictive than required — the practice allows access with supervision, not only after vetting.',
    mindsetNote: 'Long-term vendors are often the weakest link in physical security because familiarity breeds complacency. "We\'ve worked with them for 15 years" is the same rationalization that enables insider threat and social engineering. MA.L2-3.7.6 does not have a tenure exception. The supervisor requirement applies to any maintenance personnel without proper access authorization — and proper authorization means a documented, current background check, not familiarity.',
