    explanation: 'PE.L2-3.10.5 requires controlling and managing physical access devices — which includes managing the credentials (badge profiles, PIN access) that authorize individuals to use those devices. When a person\'s role changes such that they no longer need access to a CUI area, their physical access authorization must be revoked promptly. "They might need it someday" is not a documented business need — it is indefinitely deferred access removal. This is the physical access analog to IA.L2-3.5.6 (disable inactive logical identifiers). Both practices share the same principle: access that is no longer needed must be removed.',
    mindsetNote: 'Physical and logical access revocation must happen together when employees change roles or leave. Organizations that have strong logical access deprovisioning processes often neglect physical access. An assessor will request the active badge access list and compare it to current role assignments. Former employees with active badge profiles and transferred employees with access beyond their current role are both findings.',
