    mindsetNote: 'Independence in assessment is a core quality principle. At L2, the CMMC assessment itself provides third-party validation, but the ongoing CA.L2-3.12.1 requirement for periodic internal assessments still benefits from independence. Best practice is to have someone other than the implementer perform or review the assessment — a different team member, an internal audit function, or an external consultant. The IT manager checking their own work is the weakest possible evidence of control effectiveness.',
