    mindsetNote: 'Clock synchronization is often treated as an IT hygiene issue rather than a security control, but it is a direct enabler of forensic capability. During incident response, a 17-minute timestamp offset can make the difference between understanding the attack chain and drawing the wrong conclusions. Assessors should verify that NTP is configured on all in-scope systems and synchronized to the same authoritative source.',
