    explanation: 'AU.L2-3.3.8 requires protecting audit logs and audit tools from unauthorized modification or deletion. A local admin being able to delete the event log means the audit record is not protected. Proper implementation requires: (1) forwarding logs to a remote log server or SIEM in near-real-time so local deletion cannot erase the record, (2) restricting who can clear event logs — local admin rights should not automatically confer the ability to delete audit records. The attacker exploited the gap between when the log was created and when it was protected. Option D (AC.L2-3.1.7) is relevant to why the insider had admin rights, but the specific audit protection failure is 3.3.8.',
