    explanation: 'NIST SP 800-171 §3.6.1 requires an "operational" incident-handling capability but does not prescribe team size, staffing structure, or headcount. For small organizations, a capability that includes: a written plan covering all six phases, assigned roles with backups, and access to external IR support satisfies the requirement. The MSSP retainer is a recognized form of external IR capability. Options A and D impose requirements not stated in 800-171. Option C creates an arbitrary headcount requirement that has no basis in the standard.',
    mindsetNote: 'CMMC is scalable — the same practice applies to a 5-person contractor and a 5,000-person prime. "Operational" means the capability is documented, assigned, and exercisable — not that it requires dedicated headcount. Small contractors should document relationships with external IR providers as part of their capability. During assessment, verify: is the plan known to the personnel responsible? Can they actually invoke it?',
    sourceRef: 'NIST SP 800-171 Rev 2 §3.6.1',
