    mindsetNote: 'Privilege escalation over a remote session combines two high-risk factors: remote access (outside physical control) and privileged capability. AC.L2-3.1.15 requires that this combination be specifically documented and authorized — not just allowed as a convenience. Assessors should request the list of authorized privileged remote access capabilities from the SSP and verify they are limited to documented operational needs.',
