    explanation: 'CM.L2-3.4.1 requires establishing and maintaining baseline configurations of the systems. Maintaining means keeping the baseline current — a baseline that has not been updated after a major OS upgrade no longer reflects the approved configuration of the system. Assessors look for version-controlled baseline documentation that matches what is actually running. A stale baseline provides false assurance: it appears to define the approved configuration but cannot be used to detect or remediate deviations because it does not describe the current system.',
    mindsetNote: 'A baseline that does not match current production is not a baseline — it is a historical artifact. CM.L2-3.4.1 requires the baseline to be a living document updated with approved changes. Assessors should compare the documented baseline against actual system configurations (OS version, installed packages, running services) to verify accuracy. Significant discrepancies are findings against 3.4.1.',
