    mindsetNote: 'Physical controls and cryptographic controls are not mutually exclusive — they are complementary. MP.L2-3.8.6 addresses the scenario where physical controls fail or are bypassed. If a drive is stolen from a server during a maintenance visit, or if a recycled drive is not properly sanitized, encryption at rest ensures the data is still protected. Assessors should check whether CUI at rest uses encryption, independent of what physical controls exist around the storage.',
