    mindsetNote: 'Role-based training is not optional for high-privilege users. AT.L2-3.2.2 recognizes that personnel with elevated access or security functions face different risks and have different obligations than general users. Assessors should identify who has privileged access or security responsibilities (DBAs, sysadmins, security personnel, incident responders) and verify they receive training specific to those roles, documented and tracked separately from general awareness.',
